article.headline: Northeastern has no answer for Eagles' spurts
article.linkText: No. 18 BC gets rolling early, runs roughshod over Northeastern
article.story:
BOSTON (AP) -- Amber Jacobs had 18 points for Boston College (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP), which scored the game's first nine and opened the second half with a 25-3 run while beating Northeastern 86-48 Thursday night.

The Eagles (5-1) held Northeastern 19 points below its average, and outrebounded the Huskies 44-28. The Huskies (2-5) cut the lead to 18-11 on Aisha Williams' 3-pointer with 12:50 left in the half, but it took the Eagles just 2:30 to make it 27-11.

Northeastern, which has now lost three consecutive games, got no closer than a 10-point deficit thereafter. Boston College led 40-29 at halftime.

Williams led the Huskies with 13 points, and freshman Maralene Zwarich added 11.

Jessalyn Deveny added 12 points for Boston College, which got 11 points and five assists from Brianne Stepherson.
